"art\", \"from\": 576, \"to\": 579}, {\"ngram\": \"an Olympic discipline\", \"from\": 584, \"to\": 605}, {\"ngram\": \"the exhibition\", \"from\": 627, \"to\": 641}, {\"ngram\": \"Flora Vere O'Brien\", \"from\": 713, \"to\": 731}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Organisers say one of the main focuses of the exhibition is to highlight how integral art was to the early Olympics and question what is means to compete and represent your nation as an artist.\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 954, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"Organisers\", \"from\": 761, \"to\": 771}, {\"ngram\": \"the main focuses\", \"from\": 783, \"to\": 799}, {\"ngram\": \"the exhibition\", \"from\": 803, \"to\": 817}, {\"ngram\": \"integral art\", \"from\": 838, \"to\": 850}, {\"ngram\": \"the early Olympics\", \"from\": 858, \"to\": 876}, {\"ngram\": \"your nation\", \"from\": 929, \"to\": 940}, {\"ngram\": \"an artist\", \"from\": 944, \"to\": 953}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The gallery has made some exciting discoveries including Mainie Jellett's 'The Bathers/Baigneurs' artwork that was painted in 1922, but only recently has been identified as featuring in the 1928 Amsterdam Olympics.\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 1170, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1013, \"end\": 1027, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainie_Jellett\", \"score\": 1.0, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Mainie Jellett\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainie_Jellett\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Mainie_Jellett\"}, {\"begin\": 1151, \"end\": 1160, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"score\": 0.9999999999522515, \"rank\": 2.494481349070736e-11, \"text\": \"Amsterdam\", \"types\": [\"Q515\", \"Q486972\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Amsterdam\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The gallery\", \"from\": 956, \"to\": 967}, {\"ngram\": \"some exciting discoveries\", \"from\": 977, \"to\": 1002}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Also, enigmatic and somewhat eccentric artist, Flora Vere O'Brien was featured twice in the 1948 Olympics with a poem 'A Song for the Road' and a print, assumed lost, entitled 'The Hurlers'.\", \"from\": 1172, \"to\": 1362, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"enigmatic and somewhat eccentric artist\", \"from\": 1178, \"to\": 1217}, {\"ngram\": \"Flora Vere O'Brien\", \"from\": 1219, \"to\": 1237}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1948 Olympics\", \"from\": 1260, \"to\": 1277}, {\"ngram\": \"a poem\", \"from\": 1283, \"to\": 1289}, {\"ngram\": \"A Song\", \"from\": 1291, \"to\": 1297}, {\"ngram\": \"the Road\", \"from\": 1302, \"to\": 1310}, {\"ngram\": \"a print\", \"from\": 1316, \"to\": 1323}, {\"ngram\": \"'The Hurlers\", \"from\": 1348, \"to\": 1360}]}, {\"sentence\": \"Through the family of Ms O'Brien, the gallery has managed to locate one of the original editions of the print as well as the linocut the image was made from.\", \"from\": 1364, \"to\": 1521, \"entities\": [], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"the family\", \"from\": 1372, \"to\": 1382}, {\"ngram\": \"Ms O'Brien\", \"from\": 1386, \"to\": 1396}, {\"ngram\": \"the gallery\", \"from\": 1398, \"to\": 1409}, {\"ngram\": \"the original editions\", \"from\": 1439, \"to\": 1460}, {\"ngram\": \"the print\", \"from\": 1464, \"to\": 1473}, {\"ngram\": \"the image\", \"from\": 1497, \"to\": 1506}]}, {\"sentence\": \"The granddaughter of artist Desmond Broe, Sonach\\u00fa O'Callaghan-Broe, has located a treasure trove of his work including his 1948 London Olympic medal, competing certificate, images of his sculpture submitted in the 1948 Olympics and 'Race of the Gael', which was his sculpture featured in the 1952 Helsinki Olympics.\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1838, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1551, \"end\": 1558, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Desmond\", \"score\": 0.62267641438854, \"rank\": 0.6059426412883888, \"text\": \"Desmond\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Desmond\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Kingdom_of_Desmond\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"The granddaughter\", \"from\": 1523, \"to\": 1540}, {\"ngram\": \"Sonach\\u00fa O'Callaghan-Broe\", \"from\": 1565, \"to\": 1589}, {\"ngram\": \"a treasure trove\", \"from\": 1603, \"to\": 1619}, {\"ngram\": \"his work\", \"from\": 1623, \"to\": 1631}, {\"ngram\": \"his 1948 London Olympic medal\", \"from\": 1642, \"to\": 1671}, {\"ngram\": \", competing certificate\", \"from\": 1671, \"to\": 1694}, {\"ngram\": \"images\", \"from\": 1696, \"to\": 1702}, {\"ngram\": \"his sculpture\", \"from\": 1706, \"to\": 1719}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1948 Olympics\", \"from\": 1733, \"to\": 1750}, {\"ngram\": \"'Race\", \"from\": 1755, \"to\": 1760}, {\"ngram\": \"the Gael\", \"from\": 1764, \"to\": 1772}, {\"ngram\": \"his sculpture\", \"from\": 1785, \"to\": 1798}, {\"ngram\": \"the 1952 Helsinki Olympics\", \"from\": 1811, \"to\": 1837}]}, {\"sentence\": \"As part of the Creative Ireland funded 'Muscles & Mind: Open-Call', the gallery is also to present a group exhibition exploring themes of nationality, representation, and art as competition, by contemporary artists living and working in Ireland.\", \"from\": 1840, \"to\": 2085, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 1864, \"end\": 1871, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999998012754, \"rank\": 1.9876060942827447e-10, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}, {\"begin\": 2077, \"end\": 2084, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"score\": 0.9999999998012754, \"rank\": 1.9876060942827447e-10, \"text\": \"Ireland\", \"types\": [\"Q6256\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Republic_of_Ireland\"}], \"noun_phrases\": [{\"ngram\": \"part\", \"from\": 1843, \"to\": 1847}, {\"ngram\": \"Muscles\", \"from\": 1880, \"to\": 1887}, {\"ngram\": \"Mind\", \"from\": 1890, \"to\": 1894}, {\"ngram\": \"Open-Call\", \"from\": 1896, \"to\": 1905}, {\"ngram\": \"the gallery\", \"from\": 1908, \"to\": 1919}, {\"ngram\": \"a group exhibition\", \"from\": 1939, \"to\": 1957}, {\"ngram\": \"themes\", \"from\": 1968, \"to\": 1974}, {\"ngram\": \"nationality\", \"from\": 1978, \"to\": 1989}, {\"ngram\": \"representation\", \"from\": 1991, \"to\": 2005}, {\"ngram\": \"art\", \"from\": 2011, \"to\": 2014}, {\"ngram\": \"competition\", \"from\": 2018, \"to\": 2029}, {\"ngram\": \"contemporary artists\", \"from\": 2034, \"to\": 2054}]}, {\"sentence\": \"These artists include Catherine Barron, James Horan, Ramon Kassam, Alison Lowry, S\\u00e9amus O'Brien, Noel O'Donoghue, Laurence O'Toole, Csilla Toldy, Duc Van Pham, S\\u00edle Walsh and Lee Welch.\", \"from\": 2087, \"to\": 2272, \"entities\": [{\"begin\": 2109, \"end\": 2118, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_de'_Medici\", \"score\": 0.8145006638087466, \"rank\": 0.20098702737517077, \"text\": \"Catherine\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_de'_Medici\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/Catherine_de'_Medici\"}, {\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Barron_(journalist)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999952252, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barron, James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Barron_(journalist)\", \"dbpedia\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Barron_(journalist)\"}, {\"begin\": 2119, \"end\": 2132, \"title\": \"http://dbpedia.org/resource/James_Barron_(journalist)\", \"score\": 0.9999999999952252, \"rank\": 0.0, \"text\": \"Barron, James\", \"types\": [\"Q729\", \"Q5\", \"Q215627\", \"Q19088\"], \"wikid\": \"http://dbpedia.org